<HEADLINE> Kenyan Korir Retains Amsterdam Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Sammy Korir retained
his Amsterdam marathon title while the women's counterpart went
to Ireland's Catherina McKiernan on Sunday in Amsterdam, the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Koris clocked two hours, eight minutes and 13 seconds to beat
compatriot Simon Bor, who was second with 33 seconds trailing.
Spaniard Alberto Juzdado finished third on 2:09.59.
</P>
<P>
McKiernan posted a winning time of 2:22.23, one minute and 21
seconds short of her personal best.
</P>
<P>
German Silvia Oberem-Krolik followed at second with a time of
2:29.30 and Elfenesh Alemu of Ethiopia finished third with
another 49 seconds back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
