<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-01 16:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt, Syria Hold Summit Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
held talks Sunday with visiting Syrian President Hafez al-Assad on
regional issues of common interest and bilateral relations,
particularly Mideast peace process and the stalled Syrian-Israeli
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The talks in the Red Sea resort Sharm el Sheikh centered on the
latest developments in the Middle East peace process following the
signing of a new agreement by Palestinians and Israel in
Washington last month, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
After nine-day's tough negotiations in the United States, the
Palestinians and Israel signed on October 23 the interim accord.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal, Israel will withdraw from another 13.1 percent
of the West Bank and the Palestinians step up crackdown on Islamic
extremists. The two sides also agreed on some other key issues.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are also expected to discuss the stalled
Syrian-Israeli negotiations and the possibility of resuming the
peace talks, according to the news agency.
</P>
<P>
The talks between Syria and Israel came to a standstill in
early 1996 due to disputes over the future of the Golan Heights
captured by Israel from Syria in the 1967 Mideast War.
</P>
<P>
The report said the talks are expected to touch on the
Syrian-Turkish relations in light of an agreement signed by
Damascus and Ankara following intensive Egyptian mediation aimed
at defusing tensions between the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has accused Syria of sheltering its outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) and threatened military actions against
Syria, sparking fear of a regional conflict.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to successful mediation by Egypt and Iran, Syria and
Turkey signed a deal on October 20, under which Syria agreed to
close PKK camps on its soil and in the Syrian-controlled Bekaa
Valley in Lebanon. Syria also agreed not to allow PKK to launch
cross-border attacks on Turkey's targets.
</P>
<P>
During the summit meeting, which Syrian Ambassador in Cairo
Eissa Darwish said is part of the regular meetings between Mubarak
and al-Assad, bilateral relations are also among the topics of
discussion.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian president arrived in Egypt earlier for a one-day
visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
