<HEADLINE> Swedish King to Visit Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Swedish King Carl XVI Gustaf
and Queen Silvia Gustaf XVI will start a four-day visit to
Mozambique Tuesday at the invitation of Mozambican President
Joaquim Chissano, an official from Swedish Embassy said here.
</P>
<P>
The King told reporters the other day in Stockholm that he
wanted to see with his own eyes the recent changes in Mozambique
after it gained peace in 1992.
</P>
<P>
He said, Mozambique had been a friendly country with Sweden in
the colonial times, especially after 1964 when the Mozambican
people started their struggle for national independence.
</P>
<P>
The two countries established official bilateral relations
after Mozambique gained independence in 1975.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Swedish Foreign Ministry said Mozambique is the
number one country which Sweden aids. In 1997 Sweden granted
about 52.56 million U.S. Dollars to Mozambique. This year the
aid will reach 67.14 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Sweden is aiding 13 projects in the southern
African country which covers mainly education, agriculture,
energy, industry, culture and public administration sectors.
</P>
</TEXT>
