<HEADLINE> 27 Hutu Militia Die in Attack on Kigali Rural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Thirty people, 27 armed Hutu
infiltrators and three civilians were killed in a prefecture in
Kigali Rural last Sunday following an attack on a local camp of
displaced persons (IDPs), and a health center.
</P>
<P>
"The incident took place in Rushashi and Musasa commune, about
60 kilometers north of the capital Kigali,'' Gasamagera (one
name), an official in the area, told Rwanda News Agency (RNA)
this Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At Musasa, a large group of armed Hutu militiamen who had
crossed from Ruhengeri into Rushashi, tried to raid a camp of
IDPs at Coko trading center, RNA quoted him as saying in a
special report to Xinhua based here in Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
The infiltrators killed three civilians and looted the local
health center, and tried to return to where they come from. But
the IDPs alerted villages from neighboring villages who
immediately started a hot pursuit of the militiamen.
</P>
<P>
The villagers, without any help from the army reportedly
succeeded in encircling the attackers. The angry mob killed 27 of
the militiamen, and captured a good number of others, Gasmagera
claimed.
</P>
<P>
State-run radio Rwanda reported that six assault rifles were
also seized by the villagers.
</P>
<P>
"This is a sign that the population is disassociating
themselves from the extremists,'' Gasamagera claimed, adding that
in Rushashi commune, about 200 residents who were collaborating
with the infiltrators in acts of insecurity including killings,
burning houses and vehicles in the past, have surrendered to
government officials.
</P>
<P>
The sous-prefecture of Murambi under attack has been in the
the past the scene of bloody raids by armed Hutu extremists which
since July has claimed the lives of nearly 200 people, and
destroyed many economic infrastructures, the RNA report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
