<HEADLINE> Iraqi Deputy PM Meets Russia's Zhirinovsky </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister
Tariq Aziz met here Sunday with Vladimir Zhirinovsky, chairman of
the Russian Liberal Democratic Party, the Iraqi News Agency (INA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Zhirinovsky arrived here Sunday with a Russian Duma (low house
of parliament) delegation led by Duma Vice-Chairman Mikhail
Gutsiriyev.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Aziz lauded the stand taken by the Russian
government and Duma on the Iraqi issue and stressed Iraq's desire
to promote relations with Russia, said INA.
</P>
<P>
Aziz praised Zhirinovsky for supporting Iraq's demands of
lifting the United Nations embargo imposed on Iraq after its
invasion of Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Affirming his full support for Iraq, Zhirinovsky called on the
Russian government and "all the fair people" to work for the
lifting of the eight-year-old embargo.
</P>
<P>
INA reported on Friday that the Russian Duma delegation would
discuss with Iraqi officials on means of helping lift the embargo.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi leadership on Saturday decided to halt all forms of
cooperation with the U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) for
disarmament in Iraq until the U.N. Security Council considers the
lifting of the sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council on Saturday unanimously condemned
the Iraqi decision and urged Iraq to rescind the decision
"immediately and unconditionally."
</P>
<P>
The embargo cannot be lifted until U.N. arms inspectors verify
that Iraq has eliminated all its weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has long blamed the United States and "its agents" in
UNSCOM for blocking the lifting of the sanctions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
