<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-01 18:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt's Trade Deficit Up This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Egypt's trade deficit surged by
33.89 percent in the first seven months this year compared with
the same period of 1997, an official report said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The report issued by the Cabinet Information and Decision
Support Center said the deficit was 24.18 billion Egyptian pounds
(7.11 billion U.S. dollars) this year, 6.12 billion pounds (1.8
billion dollars) more than that from January to July last year.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the deficit rise to the drop in exports
and increase in imports.
</P>
<P>
Egypt exported 6.13 billion pounds (1.8 billion dollars) worth
of goods in the first seven months this year, registering a fall
of 1.61 billion pounds (474 million dollars), while the imports
rose by 17.48 percent to 30.31 billion pounds (8.91 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Exports of manufactured and semi-manufactured goods were 3.459
billion pounds (1.02 billion dollars), compared with 3.604 billion
pounds (1.06 billion dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
Raw materials and cotton exports amounted to 774 million pounds
(228 million dollars), 2 million pounds (588,000 dollars) less
than those in the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
