<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish FM to Start Latin America Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem will start his 10-day official visits to Brazil, Argentina and
Chile on Monday in a bid to enhance bilateral ties with the
Latin American countries.
</P>
<P>
Cem is expected to hold talks with high-ranking officials and
seek ways of boosting political, economic, cultural and tourist
cooperation with the three countries in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Cem's three-leg tour follows Turkish Prime Minister Mesut
yilmaz's visit to Mexico at the end of September.
</P>
<P>
Turkey holds that establishing close economic ties with Latin
American countries will lay the necessary groundwork for
productive political cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Turkey started to activate an initiative targeting the vast
markets of Latin America in early September this year when
high-level meetings were held with the participation of the six
Turkish ambassadors to Latin America, representatives from major
state institutions and leading businessmen to outline an opening
strategy.
</P>
<P>
Developing efficient transportation links with the countries of
Latin America will be a major priority in Turkey's initiative
and talks are underway with the Turkish Airlines for the
inauguration of direct flights from Turkey to the continent.
</P>
</TEXT>
