<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Egypt Sign Cultural Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Egypt signed a
memorandum of understanding here Sunday on bilateral cultural
cooperation for the coming three years, Kuwait News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The memo was signed by Yusef Al-Sumait, Kuwaiti information
minister and chairman of the National Council for Culture, Arts
and Letters, and Egyptian Cultural Minister Farouk Hosni.
</P>
<P>
Hosni, who arrived here Saturday heading an Egyptian cultural
delegation, said after the signing ceremony that the agreement
gives a new momentum to the age-old cooperation between Kuwait and
Egypt in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, he said, will open the door for better cultural
cooperation not only between Egypt and Kuwait but also among all
Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Such cooperation will help the Arab world face the challenges
of the 21st century, the Egyptian minister said.
</P>
<P>
The memo covers the organization of a number of cultural
activities and joint projects in the coming three years, as well
as the exchange of expertise and librarians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
