<HEADLINE> Tunis Stock Exchange Index Rebounds Last Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, November 1 (Xinhua) -- The main indicators of the Tunis
stock market last week were characterized by a general retreat on
the one hand and rebound of the price index after a slump in the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
The turnover last week stood at 3.7 million dinars (about 3.2
million U.S. dollars), less than a quarter of 17.8 million dinars
(about 15.48 million dollars) in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The number of shares that changed hands went down also to
200,000 shares from 900,000 shares due to the absence of major
exceptional transactions and the weak trading level at the bourse,
according to the weekly bulletin of the exchange.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the share prices of many firms last week were better
than the previous one. The improvement reflected on the main price
index that rose by 0.25 percent last week to close at 464.63
points, compared with 463.48 in the previous week that lost 7
points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
