<HEADLINE> President of Zambia TU Congress Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Fackson Shamenda has retained
the presidency of the Zambia Congress of Trade unions (ZCTU) in
the election of the new ZCTU leadership held in Livingstone,
southern Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Shamenda defeated his rival out-going deputy president Austin
Liato by 139 votes against 127 ones, Zambia National Broadcasting
Corporation television reported Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
New deputy president and secretary general were also elected
in the pool.
</P>
<P>
After wining his second four-year term, Shamenda said he is
overwhelmed by his supporters adding that the umbrella
organization has been saved from collapse.
</P>
<P>
Shamenda accused Liato of going to Livingstone with a hidden
agenda.
</P>
<P>
The National Union of Commercial and Industrial Workers, one
of ZCTU's 23 union members, urged the new executive to work as a
team in the execution of its duty.
</P>
<P>
It called on the new leadership to help improve workers'
salaries and address the loss of job opportunities due to company
closure.
</P>
<P>
The union also urged the new executive to ensure investors
respect workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
