<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 15:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Concludes Maneuver on Afghanistan Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian army on Monday
concluded its biggest ever military maneuver on the country's
eastern border with Afghanistan, the official Islamic Republic
News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the end of the maneuver, the army commander Major
General Ali Shahbazi termed the Zulfaqar-2 military exercises as
"fruitful and positive."
</P>
<P>
He said that in the final stage of the exercises which was
launched Monday morning, fighter bombers of the air force zeroed
in on the positions of the mock enemy and the infantry and armored
units supported by air forces achieved pre-determined targets.
</P>
<P>
Shahbazi said that clearing operations by the chemical units
and installation of suspended bridge for the passage of tanks
were also among exercises completed in the war games.
</P>
<P>
Following the fighters raid on positions of hypothetical enemy
and assault of the infantry and armored units, strongholds and
equipments of the mock enemy were destroyed and bellows of smoke
covered the sky of operational theater, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier General Fazlollah Shahinrad, head of the board for
monitoring and evaluating the maneuvers, also told IRNA that all
stages of the military war games were conducted timely and
precisely according to pre-arranged schedules.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the maneuver, he cautioned border dwellers of the
security of the region and warned smugglers and "agents of global
arrogance" that they would be faced with strong reaction of the
Iranian army in case of any provocative measure.
</P>
<P>
Shahinrad said that as long as the concern of acts of
sedition and lack of security in the region exists, the forces
deployed during the maneuver will remain on eastern borders.
</P>
<P>
The Zulfaqar-2 maneuver with the participation of 200,000
troops was kicked off Saturday night in an area of 5,000 square
kilometers along Iran's eastern border with Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver was scheduled to be held at the end of September
amid tensions between Iran and the Afghan Taliban militia, who
killed eight Iranian diplomats and a reporter in northern
Afghanistan in August.
</P>
<P>
The war game was postponed after the United Nations Secretary
General's special envoy on Afghan affairs launched a mediation
mission to defuse the tensions between the two neighbors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
