<HEADLINE> Al Joyner Gets Strength from Daughter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Al Joyner
said after the death of his wife Florence Griffith Joyner that he
has to draw strength from his 7-year-old daughter in his life.
</P>
<P>
"Without them, I couldn't have done any of what I have with my
life," said Joyner, referring to his mother, Mary Ruth, his
sister, Jackie Joyner-Kersee, and his late wife, three-time
Olympic gold medallist Griffith Joyner.
</P>
<P>
Joyner's wife died on September 21 during an epileptic
seizure. His daughter Mary Ruth, will inherit the legacy of
strength, said Joyner, the 1984 Olympic triple jump champion.
</P>
<P>
"Now it's up to Mary, my mother's namesake. She's the future,"
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
