<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Host Second D-8 Summit Next March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Foreign Minister Abdus
Samad Azad Monday said at a press briefing that the second summit
of the D-8 will be held in Dhaka sometime in March next year.
</P>
<P>
The summit was scheduled to be held in Dhaka in November, but
was postponed due to the devastating flood in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The D-8, launched in Istanbul in May 1997, groups Bangladesh,
Turkey, Pakistan, Iran, Egypt, Nigeria, Indonesia and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
At the press conference, the foreign minister also disclosed
that the ministerial level meeting of the BIMSTEC
(Bangladesh-India-Myanmar-Sri Lanka-Thailand Economic
Cooperation), another newly-launched regional economic grouping,
would also be held in Dhaka on December 17-19.
</P>
<P>
The BIMSTEC meeting was also due to be held in Dhaka in
October, but it was put off on account of the catastrophic flood
in Bangladesh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
