<HEADLINE> IBF To Question Indonesian Shuttler in Doping Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The International Badminton
Federation (IBF) will meet world doubles champion shuttler Sigit
Budiarto of Indonesia in Singapore in a investigation about a
doping charge against him, an IBF spokesman told reporters here Mo
nday.
</P>
<P>
Justian Suhandinata, the IBF vice president, said the meeting
would take place in the mid-November in Singapore where the IBF
would be represented by amongst others Jeff Robson, Punch Gunalan
and Dr. Myalaysin while Sigit would be accompanied by Agus
Wirahadikusumah, MF Siregar and Dr. Michael Triangto.
</P>
<P>
Sigit allegedly took a forbidden drug before playing in a
Singapore Open event.
</P>
<P>
The meeting would be a follow-up on the evaluation the IBF had
made on the results of a doping test conducted on Sigit at a
laboratory in Beijing, China, on October 22 last year.
</P>
<P>
"The test showed a sample of Sigit's urine to positively
contain nandrolone", Justian said, adding that at the meeting in
Singapore, Sigit would among other things be asked where or from
whom he had obtained the drug.
</P>
<P>
About the punishment Sigit could receive, Justian said it
would be a maximum of two years' suspension, but extenuating
circumstances could be considered to lighten it.
</P>
<P>
"Sigit's punishment could be reduced, for instance, if he
confesses to have unintentionally taken the drug, or if it's
proven the IBF had failed to properly inform athletes on what
drugs fall within the doping category," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
