<HEADLINE> China Delegation Leaves to Attend Conference of World Audit Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of Chinese
auditors left here today bound for Uruguay to attend the 16th
conference of the International Organization of Supreme Audit
Institutions (INTOSAI).
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held in Montevideo from November 7
to 14, and the delegation will attend it at the invitation of the
Audit Tribunal of Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Headed by Li Jinhua, auditor general of the Chinese National
Audit Office, the delegation will visit Pakistan at the invitation
of the Office of the Auditor General of Pakistan on its way to
Montevideo.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation will also visit Brazil at the
invitation of the Audit Tribunal of Brazil, after the conclusion
of the 16th INTOSAI congress, according to sources with the
National Audit Office.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1953 in Havana, the INTOSAI holds its conference
every three years. China joined the body in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The INTOSAI aims to promote the exchange of views and
experiences among world auditing offices in the sphere of public
finance control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
