<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts International Oil-Gas Industry Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth International Oil and
Gas Exhibition which opened today in the Chinese capital features
the latest oil and gas technology and equipment offered by 80 oil
companies from 20 countries.
</P>
<P>
An official from the China Petroleum Society, sponsor of the
exhibition, pointed out that the event is the largest of its kind
in history and offers state-of-the-art technology and equipment
available to the oil and gas industry.
</P>
<P>
Items on display cover wide-ranging areas, including oil-gas
exploration and development, drilling, oil extracting, oil-gas
pipelines and transportation, oil reservoir characterization,
petroleum engineering materials, environmental protection and
petroleum software applications.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition has attracted major oil companies from countries
throughout the world, including Australia, Brazil, Canada, Egypt,
France, Germany, Russia, Singapore, Thailand, Turkey, the United
Arab Emirates, UK, USA, Venezuela and China.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the exhibition note the importance and
significance of relying on advanced technology and equipment to
promote the oil and gas sector in the midst of declining
international market.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition has provided a rare opportunity for petroleum
technological exchanges among various countries. 
</P>
