<HEADLINE> Fighting Resumed in Somali Town of Kismayu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fighting resumed early
Monday morning in southern Somali town of Kismayu between the
Marehan clan militiamen and those of the Majerten dominating
forces loyal to General Mohamed Saeed Hirsi Morgan, said reports
from Kismayu.
</P>
<P>
According to VHF radio reports, the Majerten militiamen of
General Morgan Monday launched the attack against the positions
of the advancing Marehan fighters outside Kismayu after three
days of calmness in the area.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that General Morgan was forced to initiate
the aggression after the Marehans have captured two key new
positions near the airport and outside the northern end of the
town in the past two days.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Marehans said they have deployed 10 battle
wagons and nearly 300 strong militiamen near the airport in an
effort to ban all in and outgoing flights of the town.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Kimsmayu, flights carrying
militiamen from the central region of Mudug have been arriving in
Kismayu on small Cesna planes for restrengthening the Majerten
militiamen of General Morgan in Kismayu.
</P>
<P>
According to confirmed reports, two battle wagons belonging to
the Marehans have been captured by the Majerten clansmen as the
fighting got close to the entrance of Kismayu, some five km north
of the town.
</P>
<P>
Unconfirmed reports said the Marehans have captured four
battle wagons from General Morgan's side after the fighting has
escalated.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people mainly women and children were reported to
have fled their houses becuase of the fighting.
</P>
<P>
The fighting for the port of Kismayu, 500 km south of
Mogadishu, began two years ago after serious dispute has erupted
between the two Darod subclans of Marehan and Majerten over the
power sharing in the control of the main installations of
Kismayu, the air and seaports.
</P>
<P>
In a serious battle early May, the Marehan clansmen were
dislodged from their bases in and outside Kismayu by General
Morgan's mainly Majerten militiamen. After five months long
perparations, the Marehans now seem to be well organized and
determined to regain their positions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
