<HEADLINE> Smuggling of Hashish Foiled in Jakarta, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Customs and Excise officers
at the Jakarta's Soekarno-Hatta Airport last weekend succeeded in
foiling a design to smuggle 11 kilograms of dried hashish through
an inter-insular cargo shipment by plane.
</P>
<P>
The dried hashish is worth 100 million rupiah (12,500 U.S.
dollars), according to a press release signed by chief of the
Customs and Excise office at the airport Heru Santoso on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The press release said that the uncovering of the smuggling
plan was made possible by the alertness of the Custom and Excise
officers in monitoring the traffic of inter-insular cargoes,
especially those from vulnerable areas, such as Banda Aceh and
Medan in Sumatra.
</P>
<P>
Heru Santoso pointed out that the smuggling of hashish is a
violation of Law No. 22 of the year 1997 concerning narcotics, and
is liable to a 15-year imprisonment and a fine up to 750 million
rupiah. 
</P>
