<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Chairman Meets With Belgian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese top legislator Li Peng,
during a meeting with visiting Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc
Dehaene here today, said that China values the role of the
European Union (EU) and is ready to further its ties with EU on
the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of China's National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, said that China and Belgium have maintained a
good momentum of development in bilateral relations over the past
years, with fruitful results achieved in bilateral cooperation in
the fields of politics, economy, science, technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Dehaene's present China tour would
further boost bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Dehaene said that Belgium and China are cooperating in many
areas and there are broad prospects for the two countries'
relations.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that EU-China relations have also witnessed
progress in recent years. The fact that a number of leaders of
European nations and EU visited China recently demonstrated EU's
willingness of reinforcing its ties with China.
</P>
<P>
To increase the cooperation between EU and China would be good
to the stability of the world and the development of economic
globalization, Dehaene said.
</P>
<P>
Li said China is happy to see that the exchange between the
parliaments of the two countries have grown in recent years, which
has helped increase the mutual understanding and friendship
between the two sides. The close contacts between the two
parliaments would help promote the development of Sino-Belgian
relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
He told Dehaene that he is in favor of more active exchanges
and cooperation between the NPC and Belgian parliament.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed Dehaene on NPC's position and role in China's
political life, as well as the building of the democratic and
legal system in China.
</P>
<P>
Dehaene expressed his appreciation for China's achievements in
building its democratic and legal system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
