<HEADLINE> ARATS Sends Letter of Inquiry to Taiwan-Based SEF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Association for Relations
Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) today sent a letter to the
Taiwan-based Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) inquiring about the
status of Lim Por-Yen, chairman of the Kong-based Lai Sun Group.
</P>
<P>
ARATS noted receipt of letter from Lim saying that he has been
prohibited from leaving Taiwan for 10 months due to an unsettled
lawsuit.
</P>
<P>
Lim's letter claims that the failure to settle the case has led
to infringements on his rights.
</P>
<P>
Lim, 86, explained that he suffers from high blood pressure and
simply wants to return to Hong Kong to be with his family and
attend to the business affairs of six listed companies.
</P>
<P>
Lim has applied for the right to return Hong Kong to await
summons from the Taiwan court and pledged to return immediately
upon issuance of the document.
</P>
<P>
The ARATS called on the SEF to coordinate with the relevant
departments and urge them to fully consider Lim's health and
business responsibilities, in addition to instructing the related
departments to make proper arrangements for his timely return to
Hong Kong in view of humanitarianism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
