<DOCNO> XIE19981102.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Celebrates Water Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Water Festival, a week
long celebration centering around three days of interprovincial
boat races, opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
King Norodom Sihanouk, who had just celebrated his 77th
birthday, and Queen Monineath Sihanouk watched the races with many
senior government officials and distinguished guests, as well as
hundreds of thousands of ordinary people.
</P>
<P>
About 313 boats will take part the competition this year from
November 2 to 4. Among them are 8 women teams. Races began at the
Japanese Bridge and wind their way 1,700 meters to the shores in
front of the royal palace.
</P>
<P>
Victors can get some spoils. First-place winners receive
500,000 riel (105 U.S. dollars), second place receives 400,000
riel (83 dollars), third place gets 300,000 riel (62 dollars) and
fourth place gets 250,000 riel (52 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Boat races and a procession of illuminated floats, very popular
to Cambodians, feature activities of the Water Festival which
falls in the 12th month of the lunar calendar, or late October or
early November.
</P>
<P>
Under the impact of the economic crisis, the Water Festival
budget comes in lower than in past years, at 200,000 U.S. dollars.
The hope to get more racers to wear traditional outfit while
racing was also hurt by the economic crunch and provincial
drought. Boaters who found corporate sponsors would wear shirts
with company logos.
</P>
<P>
Police tightened security check and set up roadblocks at many
important entrances.
</P>
<P>
The much-loved fireworks display will be repeated, using
locally produced as well as Chinese fireworks. In the past, all
the fireworks came from China.
</P>
<P>
The Water Festival is a spectacular event across the country as
it signifies the end of the rainy season of the year, marks the
reversing of the water current in the Tonle Sap river and ushers
in the fishing season.
</P>
<P>
At the height of the rainy season starting from May, the water
in the Mekong River flows with such power that it backs up into
Tonle Sap, forcing the Tonle Sap to reverse its current and begin
flowing northward to the Great Lake which swells to three times
its dry season size.
</P>
<P>
As rainfall decreases and the water level in the Mekong River
drops, Tonle Sap begins to subside and its water current reverses
tying itself into the Mekong River. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
