<HEADLINE> Chinese State Economic, Trade Commission Minister Meets Belgian PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Sheng Huaren, minister in
charge of the State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC), met with
Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene here today. While
conferring on the reform of China's state-owned enterprises, they
agreed to make efforts to promote bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Sheng noted that economic cooperation between the two
countries have been progressing well in recent years, with some
Sino-Belgian funded and co-managed enterprises ranking among the
most successful joint-ventures in China.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes enterprises from Belgium to invest in China,
especially in the field of technological development, Sheng said.
</P>
<P>
Dehaene said Belgium attaches great importance to its
cooperation with China in all fields, particularly in the economic
field, and that his country is very much interested to invest in
such fields as industrial and financial sectors in China. 
