<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Monday due to buying on
warrants and selected blue chips.
</P>
<P>
In the absence of other potential leads, dealers said the
market had responded to Saturday's announcement that the exercise
period of warrants were extended to a maximum 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Warrants remained the day's volume gainers with further
interests in finance, property and construction-based counters.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality Composite Index rose 14.45 points
to 419.78, the all-shares Emas Index added 3.69 points to 109.81,
the Second Board Index gained 2.24 points to 100.90 while the
Industrial Index was 22.09 points higher at 811.88.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers 625 to 48 while 69 counters were unchanged
and 180 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 212.883 million shares valued at 200.681
million ringgit (52.81 million U.S. dollars) from last Friday's
116.211 million shares valued at 198.211 million ringgit (52.16
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Main Board volume rose to 202.629 million shares worth
186.536 million ringgit (49.088 million U.S. dollars) from 93.874
million shares valued at 181.189 million ringgit (47.681 million
U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover increased to 10.254 million shares
worth 14.144 million ringgit (3.722 million U.S. dollars) from
last Friday's 9.165 million shares valued at 14.260 million
ringgit (3.752 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals stood at 3.661 million shares worth 9.773
million ringgit (2.571 million U.S. dollars) from 52.893 million
shares valued at 103.617 million ringgit (27.263 million U.S.
dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.160
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
6.727 million shares, construction 7.921 million shares,
trading/services 28.364 million shares, infrastructure 619,000
shares, finance 18.795 million shares, hotels 405,000 shares,
properties 21.380 million shares, plantation 7.324 million shares,
mining 736,200 shares, trusts 42,000 shares, closed/fund 66,000
shares and loans 106.088 million shares. 
</P>
