<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed
slightly higher in a narrow range throughout the Monday afternoon
session.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index rose 15.14 points, or 0.15 percent, to
finish at 10,170.08 while the turnover amounted to 7.840 billion
HK dollars (1,005 million U.S. dollars), 894 million HK dollars
(114.6 million U.S. dollars) less than that of last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market surged 62.65 points, or 0.62 percent, at the opening
session which was buoyed by the Group of Seven pledge last Friday
to strengthen the global financial system for the 21st century,
but dealers said investors then began taking profits in blue chips
after recent sharp gains.
</P>
<P>
At midday, the index registered a slight fall of 16.21 points,
or 0.16 percent, to 10,138.73 points.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip Index added 223.48 points, or 2.25 percent, to
10,154.9 last Friday, taking its gains last week to 3.43 percent.
</P>
