<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host Int'l Muslim Trade Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 2 (Xinhua) -- An international Muslim
trade exhibition and conference (IMTEC '98), the first of its kind
in the region, will be held in Malaysia from December 4 to 6.
</P>
<P>
The event, organized by the Muslim Consumers Association of
Malaysia, is aimed at globalizing the market for Islamic trading
instead of trading between Islamic countries only, organizing
committee director Noordin Darus told a news conference here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said the Islamic trade has vast potential and should be
extended to non-Muslim countries on condition that trading is done
according to Islamic principles and standards.
</P>
<P>
So far 50 organizations from eight countries including the
United Kingdom, Australia and New Zealand have confirmed their
participation in the exhibition while 800 people are expected to
participate in the conference, Noordin said. 
