<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Stronger on Rate Cut Speculation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed higher Monday as continued speculation of a cut in
interest rates pushed up banking stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed up 25.2 points, or
0.95 percent, at 2,672.5 points, its eleventh straight day of
rise.
</P>
<P>
"The banks were all very strong on the hopes of an interest
rate cut," Sam Panetta from Shaw Stockbroking said.
</P>
<P>
The board of the Reserve Bank of Australia, the country's
central bank, meets Tuesday and could well decide then to ease
monetary policy soon after.
</P>
<P>
The share market's main focus Monday was the appointment of
president and chief operating officer of U.S.-based Duke Energy
Corp. Paul Anderson as the new chief executive officer of BHP,
Australia's leading industrial company.
</P>
<P>
BHP closed the day down 44 cents, or 3.24 percent, at 13.16
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In other resource stocks, global miner Rio Tinto fell 1.7 cents
to 20.00 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index fell 19.1 points to 1,171.0. Gold bullion in
Sydney closed at 292.65 U.S. dollars an ounce, down 70 U.S. cents
an ounce from last Friday's close.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index closed down 10.9 points at 1,053.6
while the all industrials index ended up 64.8 points at 4,682.4
points.
</P>
<P>
It was the banks that led the all industrials higher on
speculation that the Reserve Bank of Australia will cut official
interest rates soon in a bid to boost economic growth and jobs.
</P>
<P>
ANZ Banking Group, which will release its annual results
Wednesday, closed 30 cents firmer at 9.45 Australian dollars, and
National Australia Bank, which posts its final figures Thursday,
ended up 43 cents to 21.63 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Westpac Banking Corp. was up 34.2 cents at 10.07 Australian
dollars and the Commonwealth Bank of Australia was up 25.9 cents
at 20.15 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 296.76 million shares valued at 625.5
million U.S. dollars, as 654 stocks rose, 443 fell and 394
remained steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
