<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Expands Interest in Jian Sing Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank
(CCB) announced today that it has exercised its option to buy
another 30 percent of equities in Hong Kong's Jian Sing Bank,
bringing its total interest in the bank to 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
Originally named the Hong Kong Industrial and Commercial Bank,
the Jian Sing Bank is a wholely owned subsidiary of Hong Kong's
Dah Sing Financial Group. In May 1994, the CCB acquired a 40
percent interest in the Hong Kong Industrial and Commercial Bank,
while retaining the option to buy another 30 percent of shares,
and the bank was subsequently renamed the Jian Sing Bank.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the CCB said that the Jian Sing Bank has, over the
past four years, had steady growth in deposits, loans and profits.
</P>
<P>
A CCB spokesman said that the acquisition is beneficial for
Jian Sing's business operations and long-term development, and
will help realize CCB's development strategy in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"This also demonstrates CCB's commitment to Hong Kong's economy
and financial development," he added.
</P>
<P>
He also said the CCB will further expand its presence in the
world's major financial centers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
