<DOCNO> XIE19981102.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kyrgyzstan's GDP Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyzstan's gross domestic
product (GDP) grew by 1.4 percent during the first three quarters
of this year, reports from Bishkek said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Industrial and agricultural output increased by 6.9 percent and
2.1 percent respectively, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Metallurgical industry, which accounts for 40.3 percent of the
country's total industrial production, rose by 28.5 percent in
output, while the output of food industry increased by 14.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
Electricity, energy and machinery production, however, went
down respectively by 14, 12 and 5.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's total trade volume in the first eight months of
this year amounted to 867 million U.S. dollars, up 10.7 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Imports went up by 27.6 percent while exports slid by 7.7
percent, resulting in a trade deficit of 177 million dollars as
against 35 million dollars during the same period last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
