<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended gains
on Singapore Stock Market Monday as the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) shot up 58.52 points to close at 1,263.14 in very
active dealings.
</P>
<P>
Stocks maintained a strong upward momentum after the STI
breached the 1,200-point key resistance level last week.
</P>
<P>
