<HEADLINE> Philippine Government to Overhaul Farming Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Estrada administration will
undertake a major overhaul of the farming sector to make the
Philippines' small farmers more globally competitive, a senior
official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting here, Secretary Horacio Morales Jr. of
the Department of Agrarian Reform (DAR) said that he and President
Joseph Estrada discussed over the weekend the importance of
orienting the farmers on the need to meet the demands of global
competition.
</P>
<P>
He said that Estrada stressed the need to make farmers
understand the magnitude of the economic crisis the country is
facing and the great demands of global competition.
</P>
<P>
"It would be better to put emphasis on the reorientation of
farmers, to make them aware that they cannot compete globally
unless they achieve higher productivity," Morales said.
</P>
<P>
"We will reorient the present farming methods that we're doing
and the way we develop the countryside," he added.
</P>
<P>
President Estrada has repeatedly vowed to give utmost priority
to agricultural modernization in line with his administration's
centerpiece program to attain national food security and combat
rural poverty. 
