<HEADLINE> At Least 10 Killed in India's LPG Tanker Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were
killed and over 100 others injured in an LPG tanker explosion in
Guwahati about 1,959 km northeast of New Delhi late Sunday night,
police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the incident occurred when an
LPG tanker developed a leak and exploded at a private parking
around 23:30 (local time).
</P>
<P>
The fire caused by the blast spread fast to over 13 other
tankers and vehicles parked nearby engulfing the whole area.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was so loud that it shook the area like a
powerful earthquake.
</P>
<P>
Six of the victims and most of the injured were students of
adjacent veterinary college who had come out of their hostels on
hearing the explosion, police said.
</P>
<P>
Five police personnel and six firemen were also injured in the
blast. About 20 fire-tenders from different parts of the city
fought the blaze throughout the night and succeeded in
extinguishing it only Monday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
