100 million U.S. dollar plant in Subic to produce micro-motors for
computer hard disk drives, magnetic card readers for banks, and
other high-value digital equipment for multi-media purposes.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency reported Monday that the decision of
the Sankyo Seiki Manufacturing Limited to open shop in Subic
freeport, about 80 kilometers north of Manila, will help the
Philippines to transform the area into an information technology
(IT) center.
</P>
