allowing Sankyo Seiki to build its factory at a 6.5-hectare site
within the Subic Techno Park.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the Subic plant will begin next April and
is due for completion by December 1999, and the plant is expected
to employ 2,000 workers once fully operational, the agency said.
