<HEADLINE> Heavy Floods Kill 52 in Central Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains and flooding in
central Vietnam last week left 52 people dead and damaged hundreds
of houses, paddy fields and road networks, news reports here said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Due to tropical weather changes, heavy rains poured over
central coastal provinces last week, killing 17 in Binh Dinh, 14
in Khanh Hoa, 12 in Quang Ngai, five in Ninh Thuan and Four in Phu
Yen.
</P>
<P>
The victims included shrimp farmers living along the coast,
children caught in the rains while returning from school and
passengers aboard sunken boats and ferries.
</P>
<P>
The reports said an estimated 9,800 houses and 18,200 hectares
of rice fields were flooded, with about 1,500 hectares of rice
fields lost completely. 
</P>
