come down from the mid-term election of the two houses of the
Congress. While certain to maintain majority in the two houses,
the Republicans are no longer certain about a large victory over
the Democrats. Thirty-three seats out of 100 of the Senate, all
the 435 seats in the House of Representatives and 36 out of 50
seats of governors are open to the competition from the candidates
