<HEADLINE> Japanese Foreign Minister Starts Asia-Pacific Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Foreign Minister
Masahiko Komura left for Indonesia Monday for a six-day,
three-nation tour which will also take him to Australia and New
Zealand.
</P>
<P>
In Jakarta, Komura will meet with Indonesian President
B.J. Habibie and Foreign Minister Ali Alatas to underscore Japan's
support of Indonesia's ongoing political and economic reforms,
Japanese Foreign Ministry officials said.
</P>
<P>
He will travel to Australia Tuesday, where he will meet with
Prime Minister John Howard and Foreign Minister Alexander Downer.
</P>
<P>
He will continue on to New Zealand Thursday to meet with
Foreign and Trade Minister Don McKinnon.
</P>
<P>
In Australia and New Zealand, Komura will also seek to
strengthen Japan's ties with them and ask for their support at the
upcoming Asia-Pacific economic gatherings to be held in Kuala
Lumpur on November 17-18, the officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
