<HEADLINE> China Eximbank to Issue Three-Billion Yuan in Financial Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The China Export and Import
Bank (Eximbank) will issue three-billion yuan worth of one-year
financial bonds through public bidding on November 6.
</P>
<P>
This will be the second time for Eximbank to issue financial
bonds through public bidding. Last month it successfully issued
three-billion yuan in three-year financial bonds through this
method.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Eximbank said that proceeds from the
issuance will be used mainly for export-seller credit.
</P>
<P>
Eximbank plans to issue 15 billion yuan in financial bonds this
year, of which six billion yuan worth will be issued through
public bidding, accounting for 40 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that next year the bank will further expand
the volume of financial bonds issued through public bidding. In
addition, it plans to launch other kinds of policy-oriented
financial bonds to cater to the needs of a variety of investors.
</P>
<P>
He said that Eximbank has established effective risk-prevention
and management systems in recent years, enabling the bank to
maintain a high bond-repayment record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
