<HEADLINE> More Palestinians Enter Israel as Closure Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 60,000 Palestinian
workers and 21,000 businessmen were allowed to enter Israel as of
Monday morning as the closure imposed on Gaza and the West Bank
was completely lifted.
</P>
<P>
The closure was imposed by Israeli army on September 11
following the Islamic Resistance Group (Hamas) vowed to avenge the
killing by Israeli soldiers of its two senior members. It has been
gradually eased since the end of the Jewish holiday of Sukkot, or
Feast of Booths, about three weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
On Monday morning the number of Palestinians allowed to enter
Israel was restored to the level before the seal.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials have said that the blanket closure has
caused millions of U.S. dollars of losses every day to Palestinian
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
