<HEADLINE> China to Hold International Science and Peace Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- China will hold its annual
International Science and Peace Week from November 8 to 15 to
promote scientific and technological development and world peace.
</P>
<P>
This year's activities in China's major cities will include
scientific and technological fairs, academic lectures, and
exhibitions and films focusing on the environment, resources, the
ocean, women and children, agriculture, and health.
</P>
<P>
Some scientific laboratories and museums will be open to
students, according to organizers from the China Association for
Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, the 43rd United Nations General Assembly passed a
resolution proclaiming the week including November 11 every year
as International Science and Peace Week. During this time, the
member countries are urged to hold activities educating the public
on the important role science and technology plays in the
maintenance of world peace and social development.
</P>
<P>
Since 1989, more than 80 million Chinese have taken part in
these activities. 
</P>
