<HEADLINE> ESCAP to Host Conference on Trafficking in Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Economic and Social
Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) will host the Regional
Conference on Trafficking in Women on November 3-4, the commission
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The organizers include the International Labor Organization,
International Organization for Migration, Thailand National
Commission on Women's Affairs and the Asian Women's Fund.
</P>
<P>
A keynote speech "Action Against Traffic in Women as Violation
of Human Rights and Human Dignity" will be delivered at the
conference to be held in the ESCAP headquarters in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The topics of discussions include action against traffic in
women and children for prostitution, regional and international
mechanism, initiatives and prospects, the role of non-governmental
organizations and international organizations. A plenary session
will be on "Towards a New Response".
</P>
<P>
The conference is expected to adopt a declaration and a plan of
action. 
</P>
