<HEADLINE> Malaysian Students Get Emergency Scholarships from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian students have
received the bulk of scholarships from an emergency scholarship
fund provided by the British government for Asian students
affected by the region's economic crisis, a national daily
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The fund, which awarded scholarships amounting to 2.8 million
British pound (4.704 million U.S. dollars) to needy students from
selected Asian countries for the 1998-1999 academic year, has
disbursed a sum of 1.35 million British pound (2.268 million U.S.
dollars), almost half of the total amount, to Malaysian students
whose education has been affected by the economic crisis, the
local English Daily "New Straits Times" said.
</P>
