<HEADLINE> Hurricane Mitch Leaves Over 1,000 Dead in Central America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, Nicaragua, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,000 people
were confirmed dead in Central America Sunday after heavy rains
brought by hurricane Mitch ripped through the area.
</P>
<P>
Official reports have put the death toll at 254 in Honduras,
696 in Nicaragua, 144 in El Salvador, 21 in Guatemala and seven in
Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
Across Nicaragua, flood waters cut off many roads and bridges
and destroyed thousands of homes.
</P>
<P>
A lake in a volcano crater in northern Nicaragua overflowed on
Friday and sent mud and rock roaring down on villages below.
</P>
<P>
By Sunday, over 400 people were reportedly confirmed dead in
the flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
In Honduras, officials appealed for emergency relief supplies
for the more than 1.5 million people evacuated or stranded by the
storm.
</P>
<P>
Authorities throughout the region called for aid as rescue
workers struggled to bring food and medical supplies to the tens
of thousands of people left homeless by Mitch. 
</P>
