<HEADLINE> Beach Resort Becomes Greener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Sanya, a beach resort on the
provincial island of Hainan, is becoming greener.
</P>
<P>
With its blue waters and silky beaches, Sanya at the southern tip
of the Hainan Island is known as the "Hawaii of the Orient" and
is one of the most popular tourist destinations in China.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that by June the city had had 790
hectares of trees and 830 hectares of green areas, with forest
cover approaching 50 percent and per capita public greenery
reaching 10 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The city has accelerated its afforestation drive in recent
years. Last year, over 4,000 coconut trees were planted to form a
"Coconut Tree Dream Corridor" along the major beach front, in
addition to 30,000 square meters of lawns and over 6,600
hectares of trees planted on the surrounding mountains. 
