<HEADLINE> Thai Opposition ready to Grill Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai opposition claims it
has plenty of ammunition to grill the government at a censure
debate planned for late this month.
</P>
<P>
Chalerm Yubamrung, deputy leader of the New Aspiration Party,
was quoted Monday by the Bangkok Post as saying that his party has
told its MPs to gather information to grill heavyweight ministers
involved in shady deals.
</P>
<P>
However, it has yet to decide whether it should censure the
entire cabinet or individual ministers.
</P>
<P>
"now, we have a list of targeted ministers. We have already
delegated duties to our debaters. During the debate, we will show
the public how these ministers have been involved in shady deals,"
Chalerm said.
</P>
<P>
"the economic problems remain unresolved. The export volume is
low. There is no foreign investment. How can our baht become
strong? This show that the government doesn't know how to handle
the economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the opposition wanted to inspect the work of the
government, not to overthrow it.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, New Aspiration Secretary-General Sanoh Thienthong
said both options--grilling the entire cabinet or individual
ministers in the censure debate--will affect Prime Minister Chuan
Leekpai, in his capacity as head of the coalition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
