<HEADLINE> Lanzhou Provides Automobile Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank
(CCB) Lanzhou Branch has begun granting automobile loans in
Northwest China's Gansu Province, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The CCB began offering automobile loans in October at its
Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou branches with approval by the
People's Bank of China, the first time a state-owned commercial
bank has offered such service.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that presently seven industrial enterprise
groups have signed agreements with the CCB local bank,
including the First Auto Works Group and the Shanghai Automotive
Industry Corp. Individuals and firms have also shown interest in
the new service.
</P>
<P>
The bank extended its automobile loans after extensive market
research and feasibility studies, a bank spokesman said. 
</P>
