<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rare White Marble Forest Discovered in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Geologists have discovered a
rare white marble forest more than 400 million years old in
Guangling County in northern China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The white marble forest, unique in China, is located on a
2,175-meter-high mountain about 250 kilometers from Taiyuan, the
provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Qian Fan, a specialist from the Chinese Academy of Geological
Sciences, said after field investigations with his colleagues that
the forest is several hundred meters long and dozens of meters
wide.
</P>
<P>
He said the highest pillar-shaped white marble group is over a
dozen meters and the lowest about two meters high.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the white marble reserve is 9.96 million cubic
meters, making it the third largest of its kind in the world.
</P>
<P>
Geologists said the discovery of the white marble forest also
proves late Chinese leading geologist Li Siguang's inference that
Datong Prefecture, where the marble forest is located, witnessed
large earth-crust movement during the glacier age.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981102.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Citizens Withdrawing from the Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai citizens, once
enthusiastic stock investors, are gradually withdrawing their
money from the stock market and increasing deposits in local
banks, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
According to a report, deposits in local banks increased by an
average of 1,400 yuan per person in the first half this year, 4.5
times that for the same period last year. However, money invested
in buying securities dropped to around 1,300 yuan, down 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that local citizens are very sensitive to
the negative impact the Asian financial crisis has had on the
stock market and tend to invest their money in safer ways. At the
same time, people are showing less interest in instant
consumption, which also accounts for the increase in local bank
deposits, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the local statistics bureau show that the
current average personal savings in the municipality are 20,000
yuan, including 2,000 yuan in securities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
