<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghainese Spend More on Education and Entertainment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai residents have
sharply increased spending on education, entertainment, tourism
and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey conducted for the ongoing International
Business Leaders Advisory Council for the Mayor of Shanghai
revealed that residents in China's largest commercial city are
spending less on food and clothing, but substantially more on
durable goods compared with ten years ago.
</P>
<P>
The survey results predicted that the consumption level of
Shanghai residents will continue to rise over the next ten years,
especially in terms of services. Shanghai residents will also
place greater emphasis on quality.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Deputy Mayor Feng Guoqin said the survey provides
valuable information which will help the city draft development
plans for wide-ranging industries, including the commercial,
service, financial, real estate and telecommunications sectors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
