<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Improve Power Supply Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) and the Shanghai
Electricity Company have joined in a cooperative effort to improve
the municipality's power supply services.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC branch will provide funding the company needs to
improve the municipality's power grid, and support construction of
the Waigaoqiao Power Plant in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC will assist the company with bank settlements and
provide other related financial services, according to an ICBC
official.
</P>
<P>
He said that infrastructure construction has been listed as one
of the key sectors for loans, and the ICBC will help branch banks
improve the loan structure, increase assets and promote the
development of related sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
