<HEADLINE> Tomba Swaps Slopes for Silver Screen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Italian skiing legend Alberto
Tomba officially retired on Sunday, looking forward to a new
career in the world of movies.
</P>
<P>
At an Italian Ski Federation event, Tomba "the Bomba" said
goodbye to a glittering skiing career and expressed his interest
in the silver screen.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Tomba, whose career included three Olympic
gold medals, two silvers, 50 World Cup race wins, is now working
on an Italian made-for-television movie, in which he stars as a
Carabinieri para-military police officer. 
