<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Open Badminton Championships End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's bid for a second
consecutive clean sweep at the Sanyo Indonesia Open badminton
championships was dashed by Yong Hock kim from Malaysia on Sunday
night.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian world number eight showed his experiences with
nearly flawless attacks and defense to crash his world number 26
Indonesian opponent Budi Santoso 15-7, 15-6 and took the men's
singles title.
</P>
<P>
Yong Hock Kim became the first Malaysian winning the Indonesia
Open badminton championships.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Mia Audina from Indonesia captured the women's
singles title by beating second seed Mette Sorensen from Denmark
with 11-0, 11-6.
</P>
<P>
This was the first title for Mia Audina this year.
</P>
<P>
In an all-Indonesian men's doubles final, Atlanta Olympic
champion Ricky Subagdja/Rexy Mainaky beat Flandy Limpele/Eng Hian
15-5, 15-4.
</P>
<P>
Flandy and his partner Eng Hian reached the Danish Open final
last week, also losing to Ricky Subagdja/Rexy Mainaky.
</P>
<P>
In the women's doubles, top seed Elysa/Deyana from Indonesia
walked an uneasy path before securing a 7-15, 17-15, 15-7 win
over second seed Marlene Thomsen/Rikke Olsen from Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Defending mixed doubles champions Tri Kusharjanto/Minarti
Timur from Indonesia beat top seed Michael Sogaard/Rikke Olsen
from Denmark 10-15, 15-6, 15-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
