<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Kagwe Retains New York City Marathon Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Three African athlets dashed
off the finish line of the 42.195 kilometer course in the 29th
New York City (NYC) Marathon on Sunday in a time difference of
only 3 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan John Kagwe, 29, retained his NYC title in 2 hours, 8
minutes and 45 seconds, his compatriot Joseph Chebet finished
second in 2:08:48 and Zebedayo Bayo from Tanzania was the third
in 2:08:51.
</P>
<P>
Kagwe, in his fourth time to run the NYC course, finished 33
seconds slower than his performance last year when he had to tie
his shoelaces two times during the running.
</P>
<P>
The 2:08:12 record, his personal best, remains NYC's second
fastest, only 11 seconds short of Juma Ikangaa's 2:08:01 scored
in 1989.
</P>
<P>
On the women's line, Italian Franca Fiacconi was the champion
with 2:25:17. She was leading the course since the 35 kilometer
mark.
</P>
<P>
Fiacconi, 32, is also a four-time NYC runner. She finished
third in 1997 championship in 2:30:15. Her personal best is
2:28:12 recorded in the 1996 NYC Marathon where she won the
second place.
</P>
<P>
Adriana Fernandez of Mexico finished second in 2:26:33,
followed by Kenyan Tegla Loroupe in 2:30:28.
</P>
<P>
Last year's champion Swiss Franziska Rochart-Moser finished
fifth in 2:32:37. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981102.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa Wins Championship of Dhaka Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 1 (Xinhua) -- South Africa won the
championship of the Wills International Cup cricket tournament on
Sunday night after beating West Indies at the final of the
nine-nation tourney at the Bangabandhu National Stadium..
</P>
<P>
South Africa won the match by a score of 248 for six in only
47 overs, with three more overs to spare, while West Indies, when
reaching 49.3 overs, scored only 245 after losing 10 out of its
11 players.
</P>
<P>
The South African team will pocket 100,000 U.S. dollars and
the runners-up, the West Indian team, will receive 60,000
dollars, out of the total cash award of more than 400,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
South Africa defeated former world champion Sri Lanka at the
first semi-final on Friday, becoming the first team to enter the
final of the eight-match knockout event which started here on
October 24, while West Indies moved into the final on Saturday
after wining the second semi-final over India.
</P>
<P>
Besides West Indies, South Africa, India and Sri Lanka, the
sports meet was also participated in by Australia, England, New
Zealand, Pakistan and Zimbabwe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
