<HEADLINE> Novak Clinches Mexico Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Czech Jiri Novak defeated
giant-killing Belgian qualifier Xavier Malisse 6-3, 6-3 on Sunday
to clinch the Mexican Open title.
</P>
<P>
The 98th-ranked Novak, who struggled this year mainly due to
an early-season virus, boosted his season record to 17-20 with
this win and will see his ranking rise into the low 70s.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Malisse, becoming only the fifth qualifier to
appear in an ATP Tour final this year, upset top seed Felix
Mantilla and defending champion Francisco Clavet en route to his
first professional final. 
</P>
