<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany on Alert against Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Major German rivers were swollen
by days of heavy rains and threatened to flood several low-laying
areas in central and western parts of the country, local
authorities said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the southwestern state of Baden-Wuerttemberg, local
officials said that the Main River could overrun its banks during
the night and flood some nearby areas like the town of Wertheim.
</P>
<P>
Water levels on Europe's busiest waterway, the Rhine, also kept
on rising on Sunday, threatening the riverside areas of cities
such as Cologne and Bonn.
</P>
<P>
In Koblenz, where the Rhine and the Mosel River join, river
waters rose to about five meters above the normal level. Shipping
traffic has already been suspended.
</P>
<P>
According to local press reports, four children have been
reported missing in the flood-threatening areas on Sunday and are
feared to have been drowned in the swollen rivers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
